author: Inside Edition
description: A naked man ran across a neighborhood street and confronted residents when things turned violent. The landlord, Vietnam War veteran George Karkoc, says he heard his female neighbor scream for help so he grabbed his gun for protection and ran to help. He says the naked man lunged at him, violently knocking him to the ground and Karkoc opened fire, killing him. Karkoc is being hailed as a hero. The family has set up a GoFundMe to help with recovery costs. To learn more, click this link: https://bit.ly/4nOovOs
title: Veteran Speaks Out After Deadly Confrontation With Naked Intruder

author: Inside Edition
description: On your mark, get set, clean! The Housekeeping Olympics is taking place in Las Vegas, Nevada, for its 35th year. Teams of workers from different hotels in the city battle it out. There are events like bedmaking, cleaning up a mopping obstacle course, vacuuming and buffer pad toss. Teams snag trophies and gold medals, but it is mostly about bragging rights for some of the hardest working people in Las Vegas.
title: 35th Housekeeping Olympics Takes Place In Las Vegas

author: Inside Edition
description: Facemasks are the first product from Rini, co-founded by "Pretty Little Liars" star Shay Mitchell. The facemasks are adorned with animals, including a unicorn, to appeal to little ones. The masks have over 60 ingredients and are marketed to kids age 3 and up. But, that's getting under some parents' skin. Other moms say it encourages a healthy habit. Mom Karina Kerr tells Inside Edition she worries about her 18-month-old daughter Aurora growing up too fast.
title: Do Toddlers Really Need A Makeup And Skincare Line?

author: Inside Edition
description: President Donald Trump is firing back Tuesday at those who say his gilded accents in the Oval Office are cheap plastic accents spray-painted gold. Online sleuths have matched the Oval Office carvings to inexpensive appliques sold on the Home Depot website. Trump even added gold accents to his new presidential walk of fame. Fox News personality Laura Ingraham asked Trump about the accusations. "No, this is not Home Depot stuff," Trump said.
title: President Trump Fires Back After Accusations Of Cheap Gold Accents

author: Inside Edition
description: An Alaska Airlines pilot welcomed veterans on a flight to Washington DC. The pilot reveals a personal connection: her uncle was one of the veterans being honored on the flight. Veterans on another flight to DC got a surprise when former president Barack Obama greeted the veterans. They also got an incredible welcome in the terminal. An overjoyed 5-year-old ran into her dad's arms. He's a staff sergeant who just got back from the Middle East.
title: Special Veterans Day Moments

author: Inside Edition
description: At 76 years old, Janet Fontaine walked down the aisle for the first time. Waiting at the altar was her 81-year-old groom, Cliff. Janet says over her many decades of life, she's dated lots of guys, but nothing ever clicked. When she retired, she decided to get serious and hire a dating coach. Dating coach Gina Guddat spiced up Janet's online profile on Match.com, where she finally met her match.
title: Woman Walks Down The Aisle For First Time At 76 Years Old

author: Inside Edition
description: An obsessed stalker victimized actress Eva LaRue and her daughter Kaya for 12 years. Chilling letters to LaRue were signed "Freddy Krueger," the disfigured killer from "Nightmare on Elm Street." LaRue's disturbing saga was told in a new Paramount Plus documentary "My Nightmare Stalker: The Eva LaRue Story." The stalker, James David Rogers, was traced using DNA from the letters. Rogers served 3-and-a-half years in prison and is now free.
title: Eva LaRue Opens Up About Being Stalked For 12 Years In New Documentary

author: Inside Edition
description: Paris Jackson gave fans an up-close look at a medical problem. She said she has a "really loud whistle," because she has what's called a perforated septum. The 27-year-old has long been open about her past struggles with drug use and issued a stark warning to her 300,000 TikTok followers. Sometimes referred to as "cocaine nose," a perforated septum can often be treated surgically. Inside Edition spoke to a medical professional.
title: Paris Jackson Opens Up About Perforated Septum Due To Past Drug Use

author: Inside Edition
description:
Sponsored Content by RoC Skincare.

Inside Edition teamed up with RoC® Skincare and its partner, dermatologist Dr. Sheila Farhang, for tips on dealing with dark circles. She says one solution is platelet-rich fibrin, but it involves a needle and can be expensive. Dr. Farhang recommends Roc's new Eye Repair Cream as a non-invasive solution to help reverse the look of stubborn dark circles.
title: Dermatologist Tips To Brighten Dark Circles

author: Inside Edition
description: A teen held a wild possum up by his neck and brought it into the house to show her parents. The possum did what possums do, "playing possum," meaning pretending to be dead.
title: Fearless Teen Brings Live Possum Into House #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A police officer wanted to know exactly what he was getting into while on his way to a call about a suspicious person riding a bull in a commercial parking lot. When he finally arrived on scene, he could confirm the call was legit. It happened in the City of Alliance in Ohio, where they're apparently not used to seeing bulls as a mode of transportation. The officer uncovered that Gus and his human were in town for a rodeo. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Cop Hilariously Responds To Call Of 'Suspicious' Man Riding Bull In Parking Lot

author: Inside Edition
description: Melodee Buzzard went missing after cops say her mother, Ashlee, disguised the girl in a wig and rented a car in Lompoc, California, taking Melodee on a cross-country road trip.
title: Mother of Missing 9-Year-Old Melodee Buzzard Is Arrested #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: When Hurricane Helene devastated the western North Carolina region, Jackie and Stewart lost just about everything – including their 7-year-old cat, Bootsy. The feline seemed to have vanished. Recently, they heard a "meow" outside their home, and were overjoyed to find that Bootsy had returned. The cat had been a stray, so she did have some street smarts. But she was mum on her whereabouts over the past year.
title: 'Miracle Cat' Returns Home After Devastating Hurricane

author: Inside Edition
description: Kim Kardashian is hitting back after scathing reviews of her new Hulu show "All's Fair." The show is ranked second on Hulu and is the biggest scripted series debut in three years.
title: Kim Kardashian Responds To Negative Reviews Of 'All's Fair' #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: President Donald Trump ordered all air traffic controllers back to work, and said he's considering a $10,000 bonus to controllers who have worked during the shutdown despite not being paid.
title: Trump Orders Air Traffic Controllers Back To Work #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: The hat worn by actor Margaret Hamilton – aka the Wicked Witch of the West – will soon be up for grabs, courtesy of Heritage Auctions. The wide-brimmed headpiece comes to a point at the top of its 14-inch height, and features an elastic chin strap that Hamilton wore during flying scenes. The witch top was created by the Hollywood costume designer Gilbert Adrian, who was also responsible for Dorothy's ruby slippers.
title: Hat Worn By Wicked Witch Of the West Up For Auction
